BEGIN:VCALENDAR
VERSION:2.0
CALSCALE:GREGORIAN
PRODID:-//Chad Kuehn//Honorary Military Calendar//EN
X-WR-CALNAME:Honorary & Military
X-WR-TIMEZONE:America/Chicago

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:armedforcesday-2026@honorary
SUMMARY:Armed Forces Day
DESCRIPTION:Observed on the third Saturday of May\, Armed Forces Day honors all currently serving members of the U.S. military — Army\, Navy\, Marine Corps\, Air Force\, Space Force\, and Coast Guard. Established in 1949 after the unification of the military branches.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260516
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260517
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:flagday-2026@honorary
SUMMARY:Flag Day
DESCRIPTION:June 14 commemorates the adoption of the U.S. flag on June 14\, 1777\, by the Second Continental Congress. Americans are encouraged to display the flag in honor of the nation's symbol of freedom and unity.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260614
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260615
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:dday-2026@honorary
SUMMARY:D-Day Remembrance
DESCRIPTION:June 6 marks the anniversary of the D-Day landings on June 6\, 1944 — the largest seaborne invasion in history — when Allied forces stormed the beaches of Normandy\, France\, in Operation Overlord. The operation turned the tide of World War II in Europe.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260606
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260607
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:army-birthday-2026@honorary
SUMMARY:U.S. Army Birthday
DESCRIPTION:June 14 marks the founding of the United States Army by the Continental Congress on June 14\, 1775 — the oldest and largest branch of the U.S. Armed Forces. The Army celebrates its birthday with ceremonies\, traditions\, and recognition of service.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260614
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260615
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:navy-birthday-2026@honorary
SUMMARY:U.S. Navy Birthday
DESCRIPTION:October 13 marks the founding of the Continental Navy on October 13\, 1775\, when the Second Continental Congress authorized the construction of the first naval vessels. The U.S. Navy celebrates its birthday with ceremonies and fleet week events.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261013
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261014
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:marines-birthday-2026@honorary
SUMMARY:U.S. Marine Corps Birthday
DESCRIPTION:November 10 marks the establishment of the United States Marine Corps on November 10\, 1775\, at Tun Tavern in Philadelphia. Marines worldwide celebrate with the traditional reading of the Commandant's birthday message and a cake-cutting ceremony.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261110
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261111
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:airforce-birthday-2026@honorary
SUMMARY:U.S. Air Force Birthday
DESCRIPTION:September 18 marks the establishment of the United States Air Force as an independent military branch on September 18\, 1947\, under the National Security Act. Originally part of the Army\, the Air Force became the world's most powerful air service.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260918
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260919
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:spaceforce-birthday-2026@honorary
SUMMARY:U.S. Space Force Birthday
DESCRIPTION:December 20 marks the establishment of the United States Space Force on December 20\, 2019\, when President Trump signed the National Defense Authorization Act. The Space Force is the newest and sixth branch of the U.S. Armed Forces\, responsible for space operations.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261220
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261221
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:patriotday-2026@honorary
SUMMARY:Patriot Day
DESCRIPTION:September 11 is designated as Patriot Day in remembrance of the 2\,977 people killed in the terrorist attacks on September 11\, 2001. Flags are flown at half-staff and moments of silence are observed nationwide at the times the attacks occurred.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260911
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260912
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pow-mia-day-2026@honorary
SUMMARY:National POW/MIA Recognition Day
DESCRIPTION:Observed on the third Friday of September\, National POW/MIA Recognition Day honors American prisoners of war and those missing in action from all conflicts. The black POW/MIA flag is flown alongside the U.S. flag at federal buildings\, military installations\, and war memorials.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260918
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260919
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pearl-harbor-day-2026@honorary
SUMMARY:National Pearl Harbor Remembrance Day
DESCRIPTION:December 7 marks the anniversary of the Japanese attack on Pearl Harbor\, Hawaii\, on December 7\, 1941 — 'a date which will live in infamy'\, in the words of President Roosevelt. The attack killed 2\,403 Americans and brought the United States into World War II.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261207
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261208
END:VEVENT

