DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20320615
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:dday-2032@honorary
SUMMARY:D-Day Remembrance
DESCRIPTION:June 6 marks the anniversary of the D-Day landings on June 6\, 1944 — the largest seaborne invasion in history — when Allied forces stormed the beaches of Normandy\, France\, in Operation Overlord. The operation turned the tide of World War II in Europe.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20320606
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20320607
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:army-birthday-2032@honorary
SUMMARY:U.S. Army Birthday
DESCRIPTION:June 14 marks the founding of the United States Army by the Continental Congress on June 14\, 1775 — the oldest and largest branch of the U.S. Armed Forces. The Army celebrates its birthday with ceremonies\, traditions\, and recognition of service.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20320614
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20320615
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:navy-birthday-2032@honorary
SUMMARY:U.S. Navy Birthday
DESCRIPTION:October 13 marks the founding of the Continental Navy on October 13\, 1775\, when the Second Continental Congress authorized the construction of the first naval vessels. The U.S. Navy celebrates its birthday with ceremonies and fleet week events.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20321013
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20321014
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:marines-birthday-2032@honorary
SUMMARY:U.S. Marine Corps Birthday
DESCRIPTION:November 10 marks the establishment of the United States Marine Corps on November 10\, 1775\, at Tun Tavern in Philadelphia. Marines worldwide celebrate with the traditional reading of the Commandant's birthday message and a cake-cutting ceremony.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20321110
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20321111
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:airforce-birthday-2032@honorary
SUMMARY:U.S. Air Force Birthday
DESCRIPTION:September 18 marks the establishment of the United States Air Force as an independent military branch on September 18\, 1947\, under the National Security Act. Originally part of the Army\, the Air Force became the world's most powerful air service.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20320918
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20320919
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:spaceforce-birthday-2032@honorary
SUMMARY:U.S. Space Force Birthday
DESCRIPTION:December 20 marks the establishment of the United States Space Force on December 20\, 2019\, when President Trump signed the National Defense Authorization Act. The Space Force is the newest and sixth branch of the U.S. Armed Forces\, responsible for space operations.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20321220
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20321221
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:patriotday-2032@honorary
SUMMARY:Patriot Day
DESCRIPTION:September 11 is designated as Patriot Day in remembrance of the 2\,977 people killed in the terrorist attacks on September 11\, 2001. Flags are flown at half-staff and moments of silence are observed nationwide at the times the attacks occurred.
